{"id": "EUVD-2020-8849", "enisaUuid": "b24a3290-c39d-34aa-8493-fc10cfc05d61", "description": "<p>A remote code execution vulnerability exists when Windows Hyper-V on a host server fails to properly validate input from an authenticated user on a guest operating system. To exploit the vulnerability, an attacker could run a specially crafted application on a guest operating system that could cause the Hyper-V host operating system to execute arbitrary code.</p>\n<p>An attacker who successfully exploited the vulnerability could execute arbitrary code on the host operating system.</p>\n<p>The security update addresses the vulnerability by correcting how Hyper-V validates guest operating system user input.</p>\n", "datePublished": "2020-10-16T22:17:37", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-04T13:45:34", "baseScore": 8.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H/E:P/RL:O/RC:C", "references": ["https://portal.msrc.microsoft.com/en-US/security-guidance/advisory/CVE-2020-16891"], "aliases": ["CVE-2020-16891"], "assigner": "microsoft", "epss": 0.4, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "14c39617-eaef-3e43-849e-a4690e5f4203", "product": {"name": "Windows Server 2019"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "221c61dc-f5f3-3971-b013-c5ac65223854", "product": {"name": "Windows 10 Version 1709"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "33c4bd88-9674-3b0f-8a9e-a3151030460e", "product": {"name": "Windows Server 2008 R2 Service Pack 1"}, "product_version": "6.1.0 <publication"}, {"id": "3d462263-08cd-3395-b814-5b9fcf2a067e", "product": {"name": "Windows Server 2008  Service Pack 2"}, "product_version": "6.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "54ec6e20-7c68-3c81-9d99-39cadce8fe67", "product": {"name": "Windows 10 Version 1903 for x64-based Systems"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "60394adf-de9d-3600-a37f-961dc6dc546b", "product": {"name": "Windows Server 2012 R2 (Server Core installation)"}, "product_version": "6.3.0 <publicati